    <note>Lin Yin [11575] Recommended in 1204 and two times more in xiang, and finally earned the jinshi in 1226, but never took office. Only one daughter and no sons. CHECK for adoption of Liu Kezhuang's [3595] younger brother's son arranged by Fang Zhuo [11290]. Fujian TZ, 150.2b identifies him as a great grandson of a Lin Shen (not in dataset), but the closest cross-reference in Fujian TZ was a Lin Shenzhi (not in dataset) who earned the jinshi in 1076 and is identified as the 5th generation descendant of a Tang dynasty investigating censor, Lin Dang, whose name I can find nowhere! [Fujian TZ, 147.27b]. Since we have funerary inscriptions for both Yun and his brother Shi [11576] and both identify the great grandfather as Yu [11447], I assume that identification to be correct and that Shen or Shenzhi was, at best, a great great grandfather. Liu Kezhuang, WJ, 160.11a-12a. CBD, 2, 1347.</note>
